And if you’re Christian, then how Christians should be? We all have our flaws. We can work towards bettering ourselves, given a level of self-awareness.

I like to believe that Gabe and Jess have a good relationship, one based on similar values. If this is so, and we do not know the inner workings of their world, then if Jess truly has a problem with Gabe and how he interjects into conversations, she will address it with him. Honestly. Compassionately. Lovingly. And most importantly, with the purpose in finding the path that helps them grow and learn together.

Best wishes to all for the future, and to Gabe, Jess, and Milo.
